Comment: My opponent uses a popular opening: King's pawn opening.
I reply, almost mirroring my opponent.
I open up my bishop quickly.
Now my queen, I see that my opponent is not very strong after a4, I attempt a fast checkmate. If I was really being attacking and wanting to win quickly, I would have played Qf6.
This does nothing again, he should be opening up.
I threaten his pawn, being protected by my own.
I threaten his pawn with pawn with my knight.
Blocking in then knight, now I can take his pawn.
He could of played g3 (mate in two) but he decides there's no point.
